TITLE: Basic HTTP Flow Diagram for Timeout Analysis
DESCRIPTION: A basic sequence diagram showing the flow between Client, Proxy, and Upstream server during an HTTP request/response cycle. This serves as the foundation for the timeout analysis.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/gateway-api/blob/main/geps/gep-1742/index.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: mermaid
CODE:
```
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant P as Proxy
    participant U as Upstream
    C->>P: Connection Started
    C->>P: Starts sending Request
    C->>P: Finishes Headers
    C->>P: Finishes request
    P->>U: Connection Started
    P->>U: Starts sending Request
    P->>U: Finishes request
    P->>U: Finishes Headers
    U->>P: Starts Response
    U->>P: Finishes Headers
    U->>P: Finishes Response
    P->>C: Starts Response
    P->>C: Finishes Headers
    P->>C: Finishes Response
    Note right of P: Repeat if connection sharing
    U->>C: Connection ended
```

